question: Tyler has 65 square yards of raspberry field. There are 61 raspberrys per square yard. Tyler can harvest his raspberrys every 1 months. How many raspberrys can Tyler harvest within a year?
answer:
Tyler has 61*65= <<61*65=3965>>3965 raspberrys on his field.
Tyler can harvest his raspberrys 12 / 1 = <<12/1=12>>12 times per year
Therefore Tyler can harvest 3965*12 = <<3965*12=47,580>>47,580 raspberrys per year.
#### 47,580
